<body>
    <h1>Chase Programming Language</h1>
    
    <p>Chase is a modern, high-level programming language designed for simplicity, performance, and versatility. It combines powerful features with a clean and intuitive syntax, making it ideal for a wide range of applications, from system programming to web development.</p>
    
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Simplicity</strong>: Chase aims to be easy to learn and use, with a minimalistic syntax that reduces complexity and boilerplate code.</li>
        <li><strong>Performance</strong>: Built with performance in mind, Chase compiles to efficient machine code, delivering fast execution times.</li>
        <li><strong>Expressiveness</strong>: With support for modern programming paradigms such as object-oriented and functional programming, Chase enables developers to write expressive and concise code.</li>
        <li><strong>Safety</strong>: Chase includes built-in safety features to help prevent common programming errors, such as null pointer dereferences and buffer overflows.</li>
        <li><strong>Versatility</strong>: Whether you're building command-line utilities, web servers, or graphical applications, Chase provides the tools and libraries you need to get the job done.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <p>To start using Chase, simply download the compiler and follow the installation instructions in the <a href="#">documentation</a>:</p>
    <pre><code> wget https://example.com/chase-compiler.tar.gz
 tar -xzf chase-compiler.tar.gz
 cd chase-compiler
 ./configure
 make
 sudo make install</code></pre>
    
    <h2>Contributing</h2>
    <p>We welcome contributions from the community! Whether you're fixing bugs, adding new features, or improving documentation, your help is greatly appreciated. Please read our <a href="CONTRIBUTING.md">contributing guidelines</a> for more information on how to get started.</p>
    
    <h2>License</h2>
